kiss /kɪs/

(kissing,kissed,kisses) 

1. V-RECIP If you kiss someone, you touch them with your lips to show affection or sexual desire, or to greet them or say goodbye. 吻 

例： She leaned up and kissed him on the cheek. 她靠过来吻了他的脸颊。 

例： Her parents kissed her goodbye as she set off from their home. 当她动身离开家时，她的父母跟她吻别。 

2. N-COUNT Kiss is also a noun. 吻 

例： I put my arms around her and gave her a kiss. 我抱住她然后给了她一个吻。 

3. V-T If you say that something kisses another thing, you mean that it touches that thing very gently. 轻触 

例： The wheels of the aircraft kissed the runway. 飞机的轮子擦过跑道。 

4. PHRASE If you blow someone a kiss or blow a kiss , you touch the palm of your hand lightly with your lips, and then blow across your hand toward the person, in order to show them your affection. 给…飞吻 

例： Maria blew him a kiss. 玛丽亚给了他一个飞吻。 

5. PHRASE If you say that you kiss something goodbye or kiss goodbye to something, you accept the fact that you are going to lose it, although you do not want to. 不舍地告别 [非正式] 

例： I felt sure I'd have to kiss my dancing career goodbye. 我确实感到我将不得不告别自己的舞蹈生涯。

